<item>
            <title>[DERBY-2890] Simplify handling of maxPos in UpdatableBlobStream and ClobUpdatableReader</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2890</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;UpdatableBlobStream and ClobUpdatableReader have a maxPos field which tells when to stop reading the underlying stream regardless of whether or not end-of-stream has been reached. If there is no limit, maxPos is set to -1. If we instead set maxPos to infinity (Long.MAX_VALUE is close enough), the special handling of maxPos==-1 could be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
